    <h4>What did I learn? What is the "big idea"?</h4>
    <p>I learned that the logic gates can be combined in different ways to create different logic operations. The big idea is that electronics use these logic gates to make decisions.</p>
    <br />

    <h4>What challenges did I encounter?</h4>
    <p>I had an extremely hard time building the wires to create different operations using only NAND gates and wires.</p>
    <br />

    <h4>How could this experience be improved?</h4>
    <p>I think a better explanation of how these opereations can combine would really help the experience. Also a refrence to Coder Merlin's SFTP page to help publish images will improve the experience.</p>
    <br />

    <h4>Free Reflection: How has what I've learned affected my thinking?</h4>
    <p>What I've learned changed the way I see electronic's decision making process, and the more hardware side of computers.</p>
